<h2 id="goals">Goals</h2>
<p>Goals are accomplished by following our <a href="#principles">principles</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Create pleasant and inclusive experiences.</strong> Our digital products should be intuitive to use and accessible to all, with a strong sense of cohesion and familiarity.</p>
<p><strong>Increase productivity.</strong> By documenting and demonstrating established solutions to precedented challenges, we take the guesswork and duplication out of prototyping, iterating, deploying, and scaling.</p>
<h2 id="principles">Principles</h2>
<p>Principles are the means to our <a href="#goals">goals</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Human-centered design.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Intuitive — familiar, consistent</li>
<li>Focused — no extraneous elements; knows its audience</li>
<li>Inclusive — accessible, fault tolerant, avoids assumptions on our end but considerate of user assumptions</li>
<li>Performant</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Standardized.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Consistent — coding style, design choices, how things work</li>
<li>Semantic</li>
<li>Adaptable<ul>
<li>Easy to iterate, update, and percolate</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
